me robert e linton chairman of the securities industry association wall streets leading trade group commented he represented all the things that morgan stanley stood for yet was modern enough to compete in the new world very active in industry affairs mr baldwin served on the board of the new york stock exchange from  to  and then was chairman of the security industries association starting in  mr baldwins many philanthropic endeavors included the presbyterian hospital of new york where he was a trustee from  until his death in the early s he chaired a highly successful capital campaign resulting in the building of the allen pavilion in addition he was particularly proud of supporting a small project on the lower east side of new york started by two dedicated social reformers led by william milliken dedicated to tackling the high dropout rate of underserved youth the project now called communities in schools has grown to have locations in  states serving  million elementary middle and high school students through  affiliates its proven model positions site coordinators inside schools to assess students needs and provide resources to help them succeed in the classroom and in life and it is the nations largest and most effective organization dedicated to keeping kids in school he was also active on the board of the geraldine rockefeller dodge foundation in morristown nj having been a founding board member in  and serving as president  ceo from  to  and chairman from  to  over the  years that he served on the dodge board its assets grew from  million to  million and over this period the foundation awarded  grants totaling million mr baldwin served on two presidential commissions and during his stint as under secretary of the navy he made two trips to vietnam at the end of his first trip in he recommended the navy use containers for its shipments to the area after pursuing the idea for  months the first containerized ship arrived in vietnam in  his last day of office it was estimated that containerization reduced theft and spoilage sufficiently to save the government from  to  billion mr baldwin was born in east orange nj on july   he graduated from phillips exeter academy cum laude in  and from princeton university summa cum laude in  while at princeton he was awarded letters in football basketball and baseball and was winner of the william winston roper cup in  the highest honor for a studentathlete at princeton after graduation mr baldwin volunteered for service in the navy and graduated from officers training school in december  he remained on active duty until april  he joined morgan stanley that month mr baldwin is survived by his wife of  years dorothy tobin baldwin five children from his previous marriage to geraldine williams baldwin janet k baldwin of new york ny deborah baldwin fall of chappaqua ny robert hb baldwin jr of princeton nj whitney h baldwin of villanova pa and elizabeth baldwin maushardt of santa cruz ca as well as two stepchildren mary a hack of greenwich ct and w dillaway ayres jr of glen cove ny and  grandchildren a memorial service will be held in his honor at the princeton university chapel on saturday january  at  pm he will be buried in the family plot in bridgehampton ny in lieu of flowers the family requests that donations be made to the national office of communities in schools wwwcommunitiesinschoolsorgdonate arrangements are under the direction of the matherhodge funeral home princeton njto express condolences andor make donations visit palmbeachpostcomobituaries published in the palm beach post from jan  to jan   read more listen to obituary remember share memories or express condolences below view all add message what will you miss most about robert hb baldwin view guest book  add photos  add videos resources send funeral flowers view funeral home details find advice  support funeral etiquette how to write a sympathy note  back to todays obituaries notify friends and family add the email addres